<item>
            <title>[HIVE-13217] Replication for HoS mapjoin small file needs to respect dfs.replication.max</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-13217</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently Hive on Spark Mapjoin replicates small table file to a hard-coded value of 10.  See SparkHashTableSinkOperator.MIN_REPLICATION. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When dfs.replication.max is less than 10, HoS query fails.  This constant should cap at dfs.replication.max.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Normally dfs.replication.max seems set at 512.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
